Class BoardLocation

  • java.lang.Object
    • BoardLocation

  • public class BoardLocation
extends java.lang.Object
    This class represents the individual location of the board. Such as Go, Properties, Pot luck etc.

      • BoardLocation

        public BoardLocation(int position,
                     java.lang.String name,
                     int value,
                     int[] rent,
                     java.lang.String colour,
                     java.lang.String action,
                     boolean canBuy)
        This is the constructor for BoardLocation which loads the values for each individual property.
        Parameters:
        position - The position on the board of the location.
        name - The name of the location.
        value - The cost to buy the location.
        rent - An int array which holds the values of the rent, including with all improvements.
        colour - The colour of the location space
        action - The action performed when a player lands on the space.
        canBuy - A boolean value stating whether or not a player can buy the location.
